<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='461428' id='t-461428'>even though the younger patients have fewer years</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='464088' id='t-464088'>of valuable life experience behind them.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='468070' id='t-468070'>There are several reasons for this low status</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='470298' id='t-470298'>of the elderly in the U.S.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='472640' id='t-472640'>One is our Protestant work ethic</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='475825' id='t-475825'>which places high value on work,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='478138' id='t-478138'>so older people who are no longer working</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='480361' id='t-480361'>aren't respected.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='482344' id='t-482344'>Another reason is our American emphasis</span>
